connect(uint256).notice: Helper function which connects the Locker to a program pool

disconnect(uint256).notice: Helper function which disconnects the Locker from a program pool

disconnect(uint256[]).notice: Helper function which disconnects the Locker from multiple program pools

disconnectAndClaim(uint256[],uint256[],u.notice: Helper function which combines batched disconnectFromPool and claim into one call.

fontaines(uint256).notice: Stores the Fontaine contract associated to the given unlock identifier

getAvailableBalance().notice: Returns this Lockers' available FLUID Token balance

getFlowRatePerProgram(uint256).notice: Returns the flowrate received by this Locker for the given program identifier

getFlowRatePerProgram(uint256[]).notice: Returns the flowrates received by this Locker for the given program identifiers

getFontaineBeaconImplementation().notice: Returns the fontaine beacon implementation contract address

getStakedBalance().notice: Returns this Lockers' staked FLUID Token balance

getUnitsPerProgram(uint256).notice: Returns the amount of GDA units owned by this Locker for the given program identifier

getUnitsPerProgram(uint256[]).notice: Returns the amounts of GDA units owned by this Locker for the given program identifiers

lock(uint256).notice: Lock a given `amount` of FLUID Token in this Locker

stake().notice: Stake all the available FLUID Token of this locker

stakingUnlocksAt().notice: Timestamp at which the staking cooldown period is elapsed

unlock(uint128,address).notice: Unlock the available FLUID Token from this locker

unstake().notice: Unstake all the staked FLUID Token of this locker
